📊 Sales Data Analysis: From Raw Data to Business Insights
🌟 The Story

Every business generates sales data—but not every business knows how to use it effectively.

In this project, I stepped into the role of a Business Analyst, working with raw sales data to answer a critical question:
👉 “What is really driving our sales performance?”

Using SQL, I explored the dataset to uncover patterns, trends, and insights that can help a company make smarter, data-driven decisions.

🔍 The Challenge

The dataset contained information on sales transactions, customers, and products—but lacked clear insights.
My goal was to transform this raw data into answers for key business questions like:

Which products generate the most revenue?
Who are the top customers?
Which regions or categories perform best?
Are there hidden trends in sales over time?
🧠 Approach

To solve this, I:

Cleaned and explored the dataset using SQL
Used JOINs to combine multiple tables
Applied aggregations (SUM, COUNT, AVG) to measure performance
Wrote subqueries and CTEs for deeper insights
Analyzed time-based trends to understand growth patterns
📈 Key Insights
💰 Identified top-performing products contributing the most to revenue
👥 Discovered high-value customers driving repeat business
🌍 Highlighted regions with strong and weak sales performance
📊 Revealed trends that can guide future sales and marketing strategies
💼 Business Impact

This analysis can help businesses:

Focus on high-revenue products and customers
Optimize sales strategies and marketing efforts
Improve decision-making with data-backed insights
Identify opportunities for growth and expansion
🛠️ Skills Demonstrated
SQL (Joins, Aggregations, Subqueries, CTEs)
Data Analysis & Problem Solving
Business Insight Generation
Data Cleaning & Exploration
🚀 Final Thoughts

This project highlights how SQL can turn raw sales data into a clear story about business performance, helping organizations move from guesswork to informed decision-making
